Jul 12 2009 	Excellent Value	Booked this hotel on the strength of it's previous reports and was not disappointed. The Kapok has a great location being about ten minutes walk from the Forbidden City in central Beijing. Taxis wait outside the hotel and are very cheap to travel anywhere within the city. The hotel bellhop (Tiger) is also very helpful in translating/passing destinations on to the taxis and obtaining taxis for day trips (to the Great Wall etc). Rooms were very clean and comfortable with firm beds (as always in China!) and PCs in every room. Good breakfast buffet in the morning (contrary to a previous report so this must have been improved). Restaurant did not seem to be used much (we didnt) but there are many reasonable restaurants in the vicinity including a large food centre in the basement of a nearby shopping mall. Overall, excellent value, given the price and location, this hotel would be very difficult to beat.	
