Oct 16 2008 	Good hotel good location no complaints	Booked a 3 night stay in a courtyard room for RMB928 a night including buffet breakfast for 2 through ctrip.com. Upon arrival at the airport, we took a taxi to the hotel, and the bill came to RMB132. I had printed out the hotel address in Mandarin (found it on the internet) for the taxi driver and so there was no confusion on his part as to the location. Check in took about 10-15 minutes although we were the only ones there. Upon walking into our room on the 3rd floor, I had the feeling that we'd been given a cheaper room (the room wasn't prepaid) so I went back to reception and enquired about the different types of courtyard rooms. We were then moved to another room on the 5th floor which had access to a little garden. This room was slightly bigger as well, and I was assured that I needn't pay more for it. The receptionist who dealt with my request for a room change was quite patient and friendly and even helped us move our luggage (not sure where the porter had gone).No complaints about the room. We didn't spend much time in it anyway as we were out sightseeing all day. The buffet breakfast was quite good and my husband and I stuffed ourselves every morning as we normally skip a proper lunch when we're out sightseeing. My husband had bacon, eggs made to order, toast, muffins. Other things on offer - fruits, pastries, noodles, fried rice, stir fried chicken or pork, sausages, cereals, yogurt, etc... We had two young ones with us aged 2 and 4, and since the buffet breakfast was only for 2, I gave them some instant oats in the room before we came down for breakfast, and then gave them a muffin or some banana chips from the breakfast table just to keep them occupied. We were made to sign a bill everyday at breakfast although we told the staff in charge that breakfast was included in our room rate. In the end, we weren't charged extra for it. On the last day, the staff had an additional bill for the children but I told him that I'd only given them some chips as they'd already eaten in their room so he then took the bill away. The proper entrance to the Forbidden City is about a 15 minute walking distance to the hotel but you could get on a bus from the Eastern Gate (which is 5 minute walking distance from the hotel) and transported to the other entrance for 1 yuan per person. The Wangfujing Shopping Street and the Donghuamen Night market are all walking distance from the hotel. On our last night, we stayed at a hutong hotel, the Double Happiness Courtyard Hotel, which was also very nice. If you are a first timer to Beijing and are there for sightseeing, then I would highly recommend the Kapok Hotel simply because it is a good hotel in a very good location.	
